<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-058-990  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 058 990.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Decisions  Jan 1989 v21 n1 p36(3).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Novell faces an OS-2 challenge. (Technology Trends: Networks andamp;Connectivity)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Belitsos, Byron.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>A choice of network operating systems for assimilating OS-2applications on a LAN essentially is a choice between MicrosoftCorp's OS-2 LAN manager and Novell Inc's Netware.andP;  AlthoughNetware has the stronger installed base, with more than 250,000copies or about half the micro LAN market, many believe OS-2 LANManager's speed and other features give it the capability ofcatching up.andP;  Early benchmark comparisons performed by Neal Nelsonandamp; Associates indicate a significant performance lag, particularlyin running standard applications on a heavily loaded network.andO;Netware for OS-2 is slated for release mid-year 1989.andP;  It willallow Netware to emulate LAN manager, running as if it were anOS-2 application but with Netware's file system, which a Novellspokesperson claims is faster and has advanced security andaccounting functionality lacking in Lan Manager.andP;  Otherdifferences include ability to accommodate various protocols,client-server architecture (where LAN clearly is superior) andprogramming tools, which Novell is improving.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Novell Inc. (products)Microsoft Corp. (products).andO;Ticker:    MSFT; NOVL.andO;Product:   SFT NetWare 2.1 (Computer network software) (testing)NetWare (Computer network software) (design and construction)NetWare for OS-2 (Computer network software) (product development)OS-2 LAN Manager (Computer network software) (design andconstruction).andO;Topic:     BenchmarksNetwork Operating SystemsComparisonCompetitionSpecificationsMarket.andO;Feature:   illustrationchart.andO;Caption:   Netware vs. OS-2 LAN manager. (chart)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>